## 5A — Upload/Connect pipeline (runs for EVERY user on every upload):
#   Step 1: Parse → extract transactions
#   Step 2: enrich_category() on each transaction (Rule 4G)
#   Step 3: Store with source_id, user_id, source_type, normalized_merchant, category
#   Step 4: Score each transaction (rule-based + ML if model exists)
#   Step 5: Apply merchant trust rule (Rule 4C) before saving anomaly_flag
#   Step 6: Run dark pattern detection on new batch
#   Step 7: Detect EMI patterns from new transactions
#   Step 8: Retrain ML if total debits >= 30
#   Step 9: Recalculate health score
#   Step 10: WebSocket emit to user's room → "data_updated"
#
#   Frontend on "data_updated":
#     → Refetch ALL 8 modules (not just dashboard)
#     → Toast: "Your [SourceName] data is ready!"

## 5B — FraudShield: ALL 4 sub-tabs use connected account data
#
#   ALERTS tab:
#     - Alerts from all connected sources (filtered by viewMode)
#     - Each alert: source name, account type, merchant, amount, risk_score
#     - Severity from Rule 4D (HIGH=red, MEDIUM=yellow, LOW=hidden)
#     - Empty state: "No alerts from your connected accounts"
#
#   BEHAVIOUR tab:
#     - Spend by time-of-day heatmap (from actual transactions)
#     - Top merchants by frequency and amount
#     - Weekday vs weekend spend pattern
#     - Source filter: matches current viewMode
#     - Empty state: "Upload statements to see behaviour patterns"
#
#   DEVICES tab:
#     - Login device history from auth logs
#     - Never show fake/demo device data
#     - If no data: "Device tracking available after 30 days"
#
#   INVESTIGATION tab:
#     - Drill-down on flagged transactions (anomaly_flag=True, risk>=50)
#     - Shows: merchant, amount, date, category, risk_score, why_flagged
#     - Link to original transaction in Transactions list
#     - Empty: "No transactions under investigation"
#
#   All 4 tabs MUST be populated from real connected account transactions.
#   NEVER show empty tab when there is uploaded data.

## 5C — Dark Patterns: populated from connected account data
#   Run detection on all transactions for this user+viewMode
#   Pattern types:
#     - Subscription creep (recurring amount increasing over time)
#     - Trial trap (small first charge → large recurring)
#     - Hidden fees (charge differs from expected amount)
#     - Impulse triggers (late night / weekend clustering)
#   Each pattern: merchant, amount, frequency, source account name
#   Empty state: "No dark patterns detected in your transactions"
#   NEVER empty when user has uploaded transactions

## 5D — API: source-aware endpoints
