# RULE 14 — NEW USER ONBOARDING: ZERO ASSUMPTIONS (NEW)
# ================================================================
# A new user who just signed up has NO data, NO ghost rows, NO previous state.
# The app must NEVER crash or show another user's data for a new signup.

## 14A — Two onboarding paths — BOTH fully supported:
#
#   PATH 1 — Bank Link (ghost DB accounts pre-created):
#     - User selects a bank from the link-bank screen
#     - Backend returns the pre-seeded ghost account for that user+bank combo
#     - Frontend shows dashboard populated with that account's transactions
#     - source_type = 'bank', source_id = <ghost account id for THIS user>
#     - Ghost accounts: ALWAYS scoped per user_id. Never share between users.
#
#   PATH 2 — Document Upload (bank PDF / credit card PDF / CSV):
#     - User uploads a document on the connect-accounts screen
#     - Agentic AI pipeline extracts transactions (Rule 5A applies)
#     - On success: pipeline emits "data_updated" WebSocket event for THIS user
#     - Frontend refetches ALL 8 modules from real extracted data
#     - source_type = 'bank_pdf' | 'credit_card_pdf' | 'csv'
#     - NOTHING from another user is ever shown
#
#   FORBIDDEN after either path:
#     - Showing placeholder/demo/ghost data from a different user
#     - Showing empty sections when real data exists
#     - Crashing because user has no prior history

## 14B — Ghost / pre-seeded accounts rule:
#   Ghost accounts in DB MUST always have user_id column set to the actual user.
#   NEVER create ghost accounts with user_id = NULL or user_id = 0 or shared.
#   Schema: accounts(id, user_id, institution, source_type, is_ghost)
#   Query:  SELECT * FROM accounts WHERE user_id = :uid AND is_ghost = true
#   Ghost rows are PER USER. If 5 ghost banks exist → each is tied to THAT user.

## 14C — Connect Accounts screen rules:
#   - After PATH 1 or PATH 2 completes → redirect to Dashboard
#   - Dashboard fetches from: GET /api/{user_id}/dashboard?mode=merged
#   - ALL 8 modules auto-populate from the linked/uploaded source
#   - Connected Accounts section: lists only THIS user's accounts
#   - "Add account" always available regardless of existing count

## 14D — No stale data between sessions / users:
#   - On logout: clear all in-memory state, tokens, cached API responses
#   - On next login: fresh fetch for the new user_id
#   - Never use cached data from the previous user's session


